  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Host compiler use is typically charged back to the department. The information provided from compiler usage is a&#xD;
    consideration for application modernization and for server workload optimizations.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Host Compiler Usage = (total System z/OS host compile sessions)&lt;br />&#xD;
    Desktop Compiler Usage = (total desktop solution compiles)&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    One of the strategies in cost reduction is to assess what non-critical workloads could be shifted to lower cost&#xD;
    platforms. Modern desktop IDE's such as IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Developer for System z include local compilers which can replace&#xD;
    the host compiler for less critical uses.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    As teams successfully adopt desktop solutions, there should be a corresponding reduction in compiler chargebacks as&#xD;
    more of the less critical compilation workloads are transferred to the desktop.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Host compiler use is already reported regularly in typical shops. A deployment of a new desktop enterprise IDE should&#xD;
    include a plan for monthly rollup of host and desktop compiler use.so that the cost savings from shifting non-critical&#xD;
    compilation workloads to the desktop can be observed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Host compiler Usage is directly obtainable from the host. Since most organizations already have processes in place to&#xD;
    recover compiler costs from the user community, collection and reporting tools for host compiler use should be&#xD;
    well-established. Desktop compiler use can be captured manually.&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    You can use IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Developer for System z&amp;reg; IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg; for retrieving, reporting, and analyzing&#xD;
    this information.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
